cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with action localization in videos. The proposed Tube Proposal Network (TPN) is a deep learning framework, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper proposes a novel approach for generating generic tubelet proposals, which could be considered as an Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) problem. Additionally, the proposed method can be utilized in various video analysis tasks, including recognizing and localizing actions in videos, which could also fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper uses standard datasets for evaluation, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category.
